<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The syntype YPM 1787 is a small, 5.8 cm long dark red colony of two dichotomous branches. A 1.1 cm long stem arises from an oval holdfast ~ 1 cm in diameter (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A colony B detail of branches C coenenchymal and anthocodial sclerites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442678" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5A</figureCitation>
). The holdfast is covered by a thin layer of coenenchyme without polyps. The stem is 2.0 mm in diameter and bifurcates, subdividing in two branchlets up to 3.5 cm long. The branchlets are of the same diameter as the stem, with rounded tips. The branchlets bifurcate at angles of 45°, ascending parallel and are slightly curved. Terminal branchlets are 6-35 mm long (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A colony B detail of branches C coenenchymal and anthocodial sclerites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442678" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5A</figureCitation>
). The coenenchyme is granulose and brittle. Coenenchymal sclerites are of different forms: irregular spindles with acute or bifurcated ends, some are slightly curved (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A spindles B radiate and cross C wart clubs D anthocodial spindles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442679" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6A</figureCitation>
), 0.14-0.21 mm long and 0.05-0.09 mm wide. Warty radiates and crosses are 0.13-0.15 mm long and 0.10-0.11 mm wide (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A spindles B radiate and cross C wart clubs D anthocodial spindles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442679" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6B</figureCitation>
). Wart-clubs are 0.11-0.18 mm long and 0.05-0.085 mm wide at the expanded head being variable in form with a larger end expanded and covered with thorny warts and leaf-like projections (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A spindles B radiate and cross C wart clubs D anthocodial spindles." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442679" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6C</figureCitation>
). Coenenchymal sclerites are of various colours: orange, red, and darker (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Psammogorgia arbuscula var. dowii Verrill, 1868. YPM 1787 A colony B detail of branches C coenenchymal and anthocodial sclerites." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.961.54846.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/442678" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
